# Custom Script Tool — Implementation Walkthrough

## Summary

Added a new `custom_script_tool` to the OpenAI Agents SDK that allows the LLM to generate and execute JavaScript code for complex multi-table queries that can't be expressed in a single SQL query.

## Changes Made

### New File

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [customScriptRunner.ts](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/services/customScriptRunner.ts) | Sandboxed vm executor with [runQuery()](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/services/customScriptRunner.ts#120-156) API, security validations, timeout |

### Modified Files

| File | Changes |
|------|---------|
| [tools.ts](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/agents/tools.ts) | Added `customScriptTool` export with full LLM instructions + example |
| [chatAgent.ts](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/agents/chatAgent.ts) | Imported tool, registered in agent tools array, added prompt instructions |
| [agentResponseProcessor.ts](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/utils/agentResponseProcessor.ts) | Added `custom_script_tool` to function name mapper |

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User Question"] --> B["Security Check"]
    B --> C["RAG Vector Search"]
    C --> D["Build Prompt + Run LLM"]
    D --> E{"LLM decides tool"}
    E -->|Simple SQL| F["count_query / list_query"]
    E -->|Journey| G["facility_journey_*_tool"]
    E -->|Complex multi-table| H["custom_script_tool"]
    H --> I["customScriptRunner.ts"]
    I --> J["vm.runInNewContext()"]
    J -->|"runQuery(sql)"| K["DatabaseService (read-only)"]
    K --> J
    J -->|"result"| H
    H --> L["Return to LLM"]
```

## Security Protections

- **Read-only DB**: Scripts only use `sequelizeReadOnly`
- **SELECT-only**: Every SQL query validated before execution
- **30s timeout**: Both synchronous (vm) and async (Promise.race)
- **20 query limit**: Max queries per script execution
- **500KB result cap**: Prevents memory issues
- **Sandbox escape checks**: Blocks `require`, `import`, [process](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/controllers/chatController.ts#109-408), `global`, `eval`, [Function()](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ship-ai-dev/open-ai-sdk/src/utils/agentResponseProcessor.ts#364-389), etc.

## Verification

- ✅ `npx tsc --noEmit` — **zero errors**

## How to Test

Run the dev server and ask a question like:

> *"List devices that had journeys in the last 30 days where a temperature alert occurred during the journey"*

The LLM should use `custom_script_tool` to:
1. Query `device_geofencings` for journeys
2. For each journey, query `device_temperature_alert` for overlapping alerts
3. Return combined results
